Preheat your oven to 200°C. Chop the @potatoes{450}(cut into 1cm chunks, no need to peel) and pop onto a #baking tray{}. Halve, peel and thinly slice the @echalion shallot{1}(peeled and thinly sliced into half moons) and add to the potato. Drizzle with @olive oil{1%tbsp}, a good pinch of @salt{pinch} and the @dried thyme{1/2%tsp}. Toss and then roast on the top shelf of your oven until crispy, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway through to make sure they cook and brown evenly.

Cut the @broccoli florets{200%g} into florets (small trees) and place on a baking tray. Drizzle over some @olive oil{1%tbsp}, a pinch of @salt{} and a good grind of @black pepper{}. Pop on the middle shelf of your oven and roast until charred and crispy at the edges, ~{12-15%minutes}.

Meanwhile, remove the root and dark green top from the @leek{1}, halve lengthways and slice into 1cm thick half moons. Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{60%g}. Remove the top and bottom from the @courgette{1}. Halve lengthways and slice into ½ cm wide half moons. Place a #frying pan{} on high heat (no oil). When the pan is hot, add the courgette and cook for ~{5-7%minutes}. Turn every now and then.

> TIP: You want the courgette to brown but not burn.

Add a splash of oil to the #pan{} and add the leek. Cook until soft, ~{3-5%minutes}. Remove from the heat and stir in half the @wholegrain mustard{1%tbsp}. It's now time to assemble the pan haggerty!

When the potato and broccoli are cooked remove from the oven and turn your #grill{} to high. Top the potato with the leek and courgette mixture. Next, add the broccoli and then crumble over the @feta cheese{100%g}. Finally, sprinkle over the cheddar cheese and pop it under your grill until the cheese is golden and bubbling, ~{3%minutes}.

Whilst the pan haggerty is under your grill, mix the remaining wholegrain mustard with the @olive oil{}(amount specified in the ingredient list) in a #large bowl{}, add the @pea shoots{40} and toss to coat in the dressing. Spoon the pan haggerty onto plates and serve the mustard dressed pea shoots on the side. Enjoy!